reviews.text: The old station buildings remain at Carrbridge although it is an unmanned station. I visited Carrbridge in January and the platforms had been salted. There was a departure notice board, just a pity the station buildings are not open. There are no facilities and it is a ten/fifteen minute walk to find toilets in Carrbridge.
Lovely wee station. It is unmanned though, you can buy tickets once you are onboard the train.
Tiny station no-one comes on or off . Point less to stop there
